    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>What Is Online TRT?</h2>
      <p><strong>Online TRT (testosterone replacement therapy)</strong> is a telehealth service that allows men with low testosterone to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Consult with licensed doctors via video or messaging</li>
        <li>Get prescribed FDA-approved testosterone cypionate or enanthate</li>
        <li>Receive medication delivered to their door</li>
        <li>Self-administer weekly injections at home</li>
        <li>Monitor progress through quarterly blood work</li>
      </ul>
      <p>It's the <strong>same medical treatment as in-person clinics</strong>, just delivered via telemedicine. The testosterone is identical, the doctors are equally qualified, and the results are clinically equivalent.</p>

      <h2>How Online TRT Works (Step-by-Step)</h2>
      <h3>Step 1: Sign Up & Questionnaire (5-10 minutes)</h3>
      <p>You create an account and answer questions about:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Age, weight, height, medical history</li>
        <li>Symptoms (fatigue, low libido, muscle loss, brain fog)</li>
        <li>Current medications and health conditions</li>
        <li>Previous testosterone therapy (if any)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Step 2: Doctor Consultation (20-30 minutes)</h3>
      <p>A licensed physician reviews your questionnaire and conducts a:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Video call:</strong> Some providers (PeterMD, Hone) offer face-to-face consultations</li>
        <li><strong>Asynchronous messaging:</strong> Others (Titan, Henry Meds) use secure chat</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The doctor explains TRT, discusses risks/benefits, and orders blood work.</p>

      <h3>Step 3: Blood Work (3-5 days)</h3>
      <p>Two options for testing:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>At-home kit:</strong> Finger prick test shipped to you (mail back to lab)</li>
        <li><strong>Local lab:</strong> Visit Quest Diagnostics or LabCorp near you</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Tests measure: Total testosterone, free testosterone, estradiol, LH, FSH, PSA, CBC, CMP</p>

      <h3>Step 4: Prescription Approval (1-2 days)</h3>
      <p>If your testosterone is below threshold (usually 350-400 ng/dL) AND you have symptoms, the doctor writes a prescription.</p>

      <h3>Step 5: Medication Delivery (2-3 days)</h3>
      <p>Your package includes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Testosterone cypionate vial (10mL, 200mg/mL)</li>
        <li>Syringes and needles (1mL syringes, 25-27 gauge needles)</li>
        <li>Alcohol wipes and bandages</li>
        <li>Injection instructions (video tutorial)</li>
        <li>Sharps disposal container</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Step 6: Weekly Injections (At Home)</h3>
      <p>You self-inject into your thigh or glute muscle once per week:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Typical dose:</strong> 100-200mg per week</li>
        <li><strong>Injection time:</strong> 30 seconds (after prep)</li>
        <li><strong>Pain level:</strong> Minimal (similar to flu shot)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Step 7: Quarterly Monitoring</h3>
      <p>Every 3 months, you repeat blood work to ensure:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Testosterone levels are optimized (700-1,000 ng/dL target)</li>
        <li>Estrogen is controlled (aromatase inhibitor if needed)</li>
        <li>No negative health impacts (red blood cell count, PSA)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Online TRT Cost Comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="min-w-full border-collapse border border-gray-300">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-100">
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Provider</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-right">Monthly Cost</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-right">Annual Cost</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">What's Included</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {topRated.map((provider, index) => (
              <tr class={index === 0 ? 'bg-green-50 font-bold' : 'border-b'}>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">
                  <a href={`/reviews/${provider.slug}/`} class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">{provider.name}</a>
                </td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-right">{provider.monthlyPrice}</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-right">
                  ${(parseInt(provider.monthlyPrice.replace(/[^0-9]/g, '')) * 12).toLocaleString()}
                </td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-sm">{provider.consultationFee}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2>Benefits of Online TRT vs In-Person Clinics</h2>
      <h3>1. Cost Savings (50-70% Cheaper)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Online TRT:</strong> $159-$360/month ($1,908-$4,320/year)</li>
        <li><strong>In-person clinics:</strong> $300-$800/month ($3,600-$9,600/year)</li>
        <li><strong>Savings:</strong> $1,692-$5,280 per year</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>2. Convenience (No Office Visits)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>No weekly trips to clinic for injections</li>
        <li>No waiting rooms or scheduling hassles</li>
        <li>Self-inject at home on your schedule</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3. Privacy (Discreet Delivery)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Medication ships in unmarked packaging</li>
        <li>Video consultations from home</li>
        <li>No public clinic visits</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>4. Speed (Start in 5-7 Days)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Online TRT: 5-7 days from signup to first injection</li>
        <li>In-person clinics: 2-4 weeks (appointment backlog)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Drawbacks of Online TRT</h2>
      <h3>1. Self-Injection Required</h3>
      <p>You must inject yourself weekly (or biweekly). In-person clinics have nurses do this for you.</p>
      <p><strong>Mitigation:</strong> Video tutorials make it easy. Most patients adjust within 2-3 injections.</p>

      <h3>2. No In-Person Monitoring</h3>
      <p>All doctor consultations are remote. If you prefer face-to-face interactions, online TRT may feel impersonal.</p>
      <p><strong>Mitigation:</strong> Some providers (PeterMD, Hone) offer video calls‚Äînot just messaging.</p>

      <h3>3. Insurance Usually Not Accepted</h3>
      <p>Most online TRT is cash-pay (no insurance).</p>
      <p><strong>Mitigation:</strong> Use HSA/FSA accounts. Some providers offer reimbursement documentation.</p>

      <h2>Is Online TRT Safe?</h2>
      <p><strong>Yes, when done through legitimate providers.</strong> Safety protocols include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Licensed physicians:</strong> All prescribing doctors are state-licensed and DEA-registered</li>
        <li><strong>Blood work monitoring:</strong> Quarterly tests catch issues early (elevated hematocrit, estrogen spikes)</li>
        <li><strong>FDA-approved medication:</strong> Same testosterone used by Mayo Clinic and Johns Hopkins</li>
        <li><strong>Medical oversight:</strong> Doctors adjust dosing based on lab results and symptoms</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Red Flags (Avoid These Providers)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>‚ùå No blood work required before prescribing</li>
        <li>‚ùå Ships testosterone from overseas</li>
        <li>‚ùå No doctor consultation (just online forms)</li>
        <li>‚ùå Sells "research chemicals" instead of FDA-approved testosterone</li>
        <li>‚ùå No medical license displayed on website</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Who Is a Good Candidate for Online TRT?</h2>
      <h3>‚úÖ Good Candidates</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Men aged 25-65 with testosterone below 400 ng/dL</li>
        <li>Symptoms: fatigue, low libido, muscle loss, brain fog, depression</li>
        <li>Comfortable self-injecting at home</li>
        <li>No recent heart attack or stroke</li>
        <li>No active prostate cancer</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>‚ùå Poor Candidates</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Testosterone above 500 ng/dL (not medically justified)</li>
        <li>Active prostate cancer or elevated PSA</li>
        <li>Severe cardiovascular disease</li>
        <li>Polycythemia (elevated red blood cell count)</li>
        <li>Prefer in-person medical care</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Best Online TRT Providers (Our Top 3)</h2>

      <h3>üèÜ #1: Titan ($159/month)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Budget + fertility preservation</li>
